# Fix Management Conflict Analysis — Project Reference

## What this project is

An ad-hoc analysis of Liferay LPP Fix Management tickets — a specific Jira
ticket type created when a customer's hotfix conflicts with an internal fix
(LPD), requiring a rebase, backport, or conflict resolution. The analysis was
built by Nikki as part of the Release Quality function at Liferay, sitting
under the broader Release Analytics Platform (RAP).

**The core question:** Which fixes are generating the most downstream conflict
work, which customers and versions are most affected, and what patterns explain
the volume growth?

---

## File inventory

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `FixManagementAnalysis.R` | Full analysis pipeline — Jira fetch, parse, plots, LDA, TF-IDF, LPD co-occurrence, CSV/RData export |
| `FixManagementDashboard.Rmd` | Flexdashboard (Shiny) — interactive dashboard loading from RData |
| `output/fixmgmt_dashboard.RData` | Pre-computed R objects — loaded by dashboard, avoids re-fetching |
| `output/raw_issues_cache.rds` | Cached raw Jira response — allows re-running from section 2 without re-fetching |
